# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock is intentionally tracked for this binary crate. Do not restore a
# Cargo.lock ignore rule: a previous trailing-space pattern failed to match,
# and a normal ignore rule would hide lockfile changes.

# Build artifacts and embedder model caches: never commit.
*.lance
/model.safetensors
/config.json
/tokenizer.json

# Editor and system files.
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# Local collaboration state and internal archives: not part of the public repository.
.nowdocs-internal/
.mimocode/
.workbuddy/
.zcode/
tmp/
clippy_job.log
test.log

# Environment files and secrets: never commit.
.env
.env.*
*.local
secrets/
2a-test.log
2b-test.log
2b-test-full.log
2b-build.log
2c-*.log
3a-*.log
3b-*.log
4*.log
5*.log

# Temporary isolated worktrees: never commit.
.claude/worktrees/
.worktrees/
implementation/worktrees/

# Seed-crate workspace: temporary cloned repositories and debugging logs.
seed-crates/tmp/*-docs/
seed-crates/tmp/ingest-*.log
seed-crates/tmp/share-*.log
seed-crates/tmp/__pycache__/
seed-crates/tmp/*_rebuilt/

# License-audit artifacts: local reports, curl debugging output, and Python caches.
scripts/audit_license/report.json
scripts/audit_license/__pycache__/
curl_output.txt

# Upstream raw documentation sources are intermediate fetch-and-strip artifacts.
# Rebuild them by cloning the `manifest.source_url` stored in a share bundle;
# do not commit them to avoid redundant copyrighted copies and repository bloat.
seed-crates/src/
